<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 24 at 1:43AM EST  by NWS Buffalo</headline>
<description>...BLIZZARD CONDITIONS WILL MAKE TRAVEL IMPOSSIBLE FOR PORTIONS OF
THE NIAGARA FRONTIER OVERNIGHT...
HAZARDS...The combination of a band of heavy snow and winds gusting
to 60 mph is producing BLIZZARD conditions. Visibility within the
band is ZERO. There are numerous vehicles stranded on the roadways.
DO NOT attempt to travel in this band.
LOCATIONS IMPACTED INCLUDE...
Buffalo, Cheektowaga, West Seneca, North Tonawanda, Clarence,
Lackawanna, Kenmore, Depew, Tonawanda, Amherst, Lancaster, Medina,
Albion, Williamsville, Grand Island, Pendleton, Pembroke, Akron, Erie
Basin Marina and Small Boat Harbor.
This includes Interstate 90 between exits 48A and 55.
SAFETY INFO...
Travel is nearly impossible in this area with blizzard conditions.
&amp;&amp;</description>
